SIMPLE: seclude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seclude
<hw>Se*clude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Secluded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Secluding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>secludere</ets>,
<ets>seclusum</ets>; pref. <ets>se-</ets> aside + <ets>claudere</ets> to
shut. See <er>Close</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
shut up apart from others; to withdraw into, or place in, solitude; to
separate from society or intercourse with others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let Eastern tyrants from the light of heaven⟦br⟧
<qex>Seclude</qex> their bosom slaves.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To shut or keep out; to exclude.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Se*clud"ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Se*clud"ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seclusion</ent>⟦br⟧
